  "prompt": "What are the best places to stay in munnar?",
  "response": "Munnar offers a diverse range of accommodations, catering to different budgets and preferences. Here's a breakdown of some of the best places to stay, categorized by budget and style:\n\n**Luxury (INR 10,000+ per night):**\n\n*   **Windermere Estate:** A beautiful colonial-style estate nestled amidst tea plantations. Offers stunning views, excellent service, and a tranquil atmosphere. Great for couples seeking a romantic getaway.\n*   **The Panoramic Getaway:** As the name suggests, this hotel boasts panoramic views of the surrounding hills. Features luxurious rooms, a spa, multiple dining options, and activities like trekking.\n*   **Ela Ecoland Nature Retreat:** Emphasizes sustainable tourism and offers eco-friendly cottages and villas. Experience the best of nature and luxury.\n*   **SpiceTree:** This resort is known for its unique architecture and stunning views of the Attukad Waterfalls. It's perfect for those looking for a luxurious and immersive experience in nature.\n\n**Mid-Range (INR 5,000 - INR 10,000 per night):**\n\n*   **Fragrant Nature Munnar:** Located away from the city crowd, this resort offers spacious rooms with balconies overlooking the tea gardens. It has a spa, infinity pool, and multi-cuisine restaurant.\n*   **The Fog Resort & Spa:** Offers comfortable and well-appointed rooms with scenic views. It features a spa, swimming pool, and various recreational activities.\n*   **Devonshire Greens Leisure Hotel:** A well-maintained hotel with comfortable rooms, a restaurant, and a swimming pool. Offers good value for money.\n*   **Camelia & EKA Resort:** Tucked away in nature, this resort offers scenic views and an escape from city crowds.\n\n**Budget-Friendly (INR 2,000 - INR 5,000 per night):**\n\n*   **Zeenath Residency:** A comfortable and well-located hotel with clean rooms and good service. A good option for budget travelers.\n*   **Bellmount Resorts Munnar:** Offers comfortable rooms at reasonable prices. It is located within proximity to good sightseeing options and restaurants.\n*   **Ayur County Resorts:** A resort offering comfortable accommodation and ayurvedic treatments. A good option for wellness travelers.\n*   **Nature Zone Jungle Resort:** Offers a unique experience with eco-friendly tents and cottages. Great for nature lovers and adventure seekers.\n\n**Homestays:**\n\n*   **Staying at a homestay can be a great way to experience local culture and hospitality. Consider options like:**\n    *   **Eastend Homestay:** Known for its warm hospitality and comfortable rooms.\n    *   **Green Ridge Holiday Home:** Offers stunning views and a peaceful atmosphere.\n    *   **Rose Gardens Homestay:** Surrounded by lush greenery and offers a tranquil escape.\n\n**Factors to Consider When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Location:** Do you want to be in the heart of Munnar town, or prefer a more secluded location amidst the tea plantations?\n*   **View:** Munnar is known for its stunning views. Make sure your accommodation offers panoramic vistas.\n*   **Amenities:** Consider the amenities you need, such as a swimming pool, spa, restaurant, Wi-Fi, etc.\n*   **Activities:** Do you want a hotel that offers activities like trekking, tea plantation tours, or cooking classes?\n*   **Reviews:** Always check reviews from other travelers on sites like TripAdvisor, Booking.com, and Google Reviews.\n\n**Tips for Booking:**\n\n*   **Book in advance,** especially during peak season (September to May).\n*   **Compare prices** on different booking websites.\n*   **Read the fine print** regarding cancellation policies and other terms and conditions.\n\nNo matter your budget or preferences, Munnar has the perfect accommodation for your needs. Research thoroughly, read reviews, and choose a place that suits your travel style for an unforgettable experience. Enjoy your trip to Munnar!\n",
